1. whatis - displays one line description of what a command does 

e.g whatis date

date(1) - print or set the system date or time2

2. man date

3. date --help

4. apropos - will serach through man page names and descriptions for instances
of a keyword This is useful when u want to lookup all commands within the system that contains a specific keyword.

e.g apropos modpr

modprobe(8) - add and remove modules from the linux kernel
modprobe.d - configuration directory for modprobe.
